!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

moan /məʊn/

(moaning,moaned,moans) 

1. V-T/V-I If you moan , you make a low sound, usually because you are unhappy or in pain. 呻吟 

例： Tony moaned in his sleep and then turned over on his side. 托尼在睡梦中呻吟了一下，然后转身侧躺。 

2. N-COUNT Moan is also a noun. 呻吟 

例： Suddenly she gave a low, choking moan and began to tremble violently. 突然她发出了一声低沉、令人窒息的呻吟，身体开始剧烈地抖动。 

3. V-I To moan means to complain or speak in a way which shows that you are very unhappy. 抱怨 [表不满] 

例： I used to moan if I didn't get at least six hours' sleep at night. 我过去常常抱怨晚上睡不够6小时。 

例： ...moaning about the weather. …抱怨天气。 

4. N-COUNT A moan is a complaint. 抱怨 [非正式] 

例： They have been listening to people's moans and praise. 他们一直在倾听人民的抱怨与称赞。

</div>

